column5: Yes! I started a winter training program for my rowing club. It has me working out very hard every day.

column8: Things have been great. I have found myself to be a little anxious but over all things have been positive. Work has been great and I cannot complain. How about you?

column8: Things haven't been too bad.  I spend a week with an 8 year old, so I'm definitely ready for adult interaction again.
column9: I would definitely spend an extra hour each day sleeping.  I generally don't get enough sleep and an extra hour would help a lot.

column5: The most fun that Ive had recently is doing a Rupauls drag race-themed birthday party where my friends and I competed in a competition.

column9: If I had one extra hour every day, I would use to spend time practicing piano and guitar. If not that, I would spend time studying.

column5: not really, I went home for Christmas which was good fun and it was nice to spend time with family, but nothing crazy exciting.

column8: Things are great. I am settled back in work after Christmas and restarted at the gym which has helped my physically and mentally.
column9: I would spend it working out or playing soccer, bettering myself in any way possible so that I am in the best shape possible.

column6: Yes I am looking forward to a trip to Scotland with a close friend and also a trip to Portugal during the summer with my husband and son.

column5: Not really anything that excites me, personally, however over the Christmas break our family was gifted an overnight at a local waterpark/hotel, so I took the children and spent two days at the waterpark with them - so it was exciting and fun for them, and exciting for me to see their excitement, even though it wasn't exactly something that excited me directly. How about you?
column6: Christmas break is over, so we are getting back into a regular scheadule.  I don't know of any specific thing coming up, but hopefully we will get to go away in the summer for a couple of days.  Anything coming up for you?
column7: As I mentioned earlier, we did go to the waterpark overnight, thanks to a kind gift, so that was fun, and it was fun to see how excited the children were.
column8: The past two weeks have been fine - we are getting back into a regular scheadule after the Christmas break, so that can be a bit stressful to get everyone back on track, but once it is established then everything runs smoothly again until the next break, so that's nice.
column9: Probably sleeping.... I should spend it cleaning, but it's unlikely.  If I had one extra hour to myself every day that would be different - an hour where everyone was out of the house and I could do anything I liked - I might do something creative, or read a book, or learn something new.  I find it difficult to concentrated on learning new things or creating things when the children (and husband) are all in the house being loud, demanding and needing things.  I would love some quite space to learn or to create!

column5: Recently, I have set up an aquaponic system in my home. I am raising some tilapia and growing some lettuces.
column6: My lettuces germinated and now they have 4 leaves. I am expecting them to grow to edible size. I am looking forward to having some harvesting soon.
column7: At the beginning the fish tank water quality was not good. The ammonia level reached about 1ppm. After I added biofilter, it is now close to 0.
column8: In the past 2 weeks, I have been really happy because I am able to solving some problems for my aquaponic system.
column9: If I have one extra hour every day, I would do some exercises and watch some videos. I want to learn more about aquaponics.
